We'll be fine, as long
as you do your part.

01:06:54.793 --> 01:06:57.829
I'd be fine if I had
signal at some point.

01:06:58.430 --> 01:07:00.562
I mean, we've been out now
in the middle of the ocean,

01:07:00.564 --> 01:07:02.966
with no signal,
multiple dives,

01:07:02.968 --> 01:07:05.004
and it just...
frustrates me, okay?

01:07:05.202 --> 01:07:06.405
Okay.

01:07:08.706 --> 01:07:09.941
So, you can't reach him.

01:07:10.941 --> 01:07:14.611
Why don't you focus on your work
and put him out of your mind.

01:07:16.615 --> 01:07:17.883
Cover of <i>Nature.</i>

01:07:20.050 --> 01:07:22.387
Isn't that what we
promised each other?

01:07:23.153 --> 01:07:24.722
Why don't you look at me,
Dani?

01:07:30.160 --> 01:07:32.398
I know all about self-sabotage.

01:07:33.430 --> 01:07:35.233
I'm the expert on it.

01:07:38.102 --> 01:07:42.204
I want you to tell me now that
this is not you doubting yourself.

01:07:42.206 --> 01:07:44.342
- This is not what this is.
- It's not doubt.

01:07:44.608 --> 01:07:48.213
'Cause it deserves the cover,
not just to be published.

01:07:49.581 --> 01:07:52.814
Searching for life that may
share the same way of life,

01:07:52.816 --> 01:07:55.153
that we may eventually
find in water on Mars?

01:07:55.552 --> 01:07:57.854
Possibly proving that
a billion years ago,

01:07:57.856 --> 01:08:00.426
the same ecosystems
existed here and there?

01:08:00.791 --> 01:08:03.795
You've touched
the limits of life.

01:08:05.030 --> 01:08:06.232
You've touched it.

01:08:06.463 --> 01:08:08.398
And now we have to wrap
our whole hands around it,

01:08:08.400 --> 01:08:10.369
and bring it to the world...

01:08:11.635 --> 01:08:12.904
and finish this.

01:08:13.771 --> 01:08:15.872
Ifremer, they've partnered
with us, there's a lot at stake,

01:08:15.874 --> 01:08:17.738
- a lot of money has been spent.
- I know, I know.

01:08:17.741 --> 01:08:19.743
Now is not the time to
doubt yourself, Dani.

01:08:20.111 --> 01:08:21.380
I know.

01:08:24.581 --> 01:08:25.617
Good.

01:08:29.353 --> 01:08:30.388
Morning, Ms. Flinders.

01:08:30.621 --> 01:08:32.290
- Captain.
- Mr. Darren.

01:08:32.523 --> 01:08:34.660
Thank you for
coming down, um...

01:08:36.227 --> 01:08:37.859
Do you think it would
be possible for me

01:08:37.862 --> 01:08:39.928
to go ashore after
the next two dives?

01:08:39.930 --> 01:08:44.600
I'm having some difficulties
finalizing my calculations.

01:08:44.602 --> 01:08:46.703
You mean go ashore
and stay ashore?

01:08:46.705 --> 01:08:48.470
The other teams
don't need you to log?

01:08:48.473 --> 01:08:50.707
- I can handle that work.
- And where would you...

01:08:50.709 --> 01:08:53.443
We would be in reach
of the Faroe Islands,

01:08:53.444 --> 01:08:55.845
after Mark and Annie,
I think.

01:08:55.846 --> 01:08:57.078
- Right?
- Yeah.

01:08:57.081 --> 01:08:59.684
I could fly to Iceland from
there and then on to Jan Mayen.

01:09:00.018 --> 01:09:03.185
I don't see why not,
if your program sanctions it.

01:09:03.187 --> 01:09:05.488
- It does.
- All right, then.

01:09:05.490 --> 01:09:07.992
We'll arrange a boat
to come and pick you up.

01:09:10.127 --> 01:09:11.462
Thank you.

01:09:20.871 --> 01:09:22.941
- Good?
- Mm.

01:09:29.413 --> 01:09:32.515
There should be a ban on
injecting the suicide bombers

01:09:32.517 --> 01:09:34.883
with drugs to limit
their ability to think.

01:09:34.885 --> 01:09:35.920
They do that?

01:09:36.520 --> 01:09:38.991
I saw it, in Mogadishu.

01:09:40.023 --> 01:09:41.559
I was really ashamed.

01:09:42.460 --> 01:09:44.095
They also do it in Pakistan.

01:09:44.763 --> 01:09:47.633
Why are you telling me this?
Why are you talking to me?

01:09:48.031 --> 01:09:50.134
You will be gone soon,
one way or the other.

01:09:50.567 --> 01:09:52.537
What do you mean by that?

01:09:56.073 --> 01:09:57.776
They will not kill you.

01:09:58.076 --> 01:10:00.309
Emir Yusef has promised.

01:10:00.311 --> 01:10:01.380
Oh, that's good to know.

01:10:01.646 --> 01:10:03.812
And there is
no one else here

01:10:03.814 --> 01:10:05.651
to talk to
with an education.

01:10:19.798 --> 01:10:23.869
So, what should we
do about the wells in Kismayo?

01:10:24.402 --> 01:10:26.872
Well, that's what
I came here to find out.

01:10:27.205 --> 01:10:29.942
The water is
too expensive for the poor.

01:10:31.009 --> 01:10:34.012
Do the local authorities have
control over all the water sources?

01:10:34.478 --> 01:10:37.014
- I do not know.
- You need to find out.

01:10:37.648 --> 01:10:39.916
You need to drive out
the water profiteers

01:10:39.918 --> 01:10:42.017
by any means necessary.

01:10:42.019 --> 01:10:43.054
Wait.

01:10:46.290 --> 01:10:49.994
Well, you need to
ascertain the depth of each well,

01:10:50.394 --> 01:10:52.196
and the quality of
the water in it.

01:10:52.664 --> 01:10:56.532
So, for example, the closer
a well is to the sea,

01:10:56.534 --> 01:10:59.838
the more likely that
water is to be brackish.

01:11:00.472 --> 01:11:04.610
<i>You have to find out how many people
are using it, plot this all on a map.</i>

01:11:05.442 --> 01:11:07.275
I can help you with this.

01:11:07.277 --> 01:11:08.910
This is what I do,
this is my job.

01:11:08.912 --> 01:11:10.014
Already you are.

01:11:10.380 --> 01:11:12.418
Here, only the air is free.

01:11:13.017 --> 01:11:15.584
Not a day goes by
without a child in my care

01:11:15.586 --> 01:11:17.822
dying of some
curable illness.

01:11:18.490 --> 01:11:20.957
The people have no work.
They have not enough food.

01:11:20.959 --> 01:11:23.729
They have no school and this is
something we intend to correct.

01:11:24.094 --> 01:11:27.598
When it rains, the mud mixes with
the waste from the latrines.

01:11:27.999 --> 01:11:31.066
I do believe with so many people
packed in such conditions,

01:11:31.068 --> 01:11:34.270
Somalia will generate a plague
that will spread around the world.

01:11:34.272 --> 01:11:35.441
Cholera?

01:11:35.839 --> 01:11:37.041
A new plague.

01:11:39.410 --> 01:11:41.479
You going to
turn it into a weapon?

01:11:55.159 --> 01:11:56.161
I am a doctor.

01:11:56.361 --> 01:11:58.197
Who keeps company
with killers.

01:11:59.664 --> 01:12:02.099
We have cholera here already.

01:12:03.268 --> 01:12:05.838
- Report it.
- Here?

01:12:06.237 --> 01:12:08.540
- To the United Nations.
- Never.

01:12:09.907 --> 01:12:12.477
- Even UNICEF?
- Especially UNICEF.

01:12:12.876 --> 01:12:14.843
Such an organization
that promises so much

01:12:14.845 --> 01:12:16.945
yet delivers so little
to the children?

01:12:16.947 --> 01:12:19.481
What is necessary is
to turn the Crusaders

01:12:19.483 --> 01:12:21.719
back from the Muslim
lands of Somalia,

01:12:22.085 --> 01:12:25.421
so that the people here can
live in a pure Islamic state.

01:12:25.423 --> 01:12:26.888
What's more important to you,

01:12:26.890 --> 01:12:28.858
treating the women and children
that come to your clinic

01:12:28.860 --> 01:12:31.964
and looking for your help,
or... Or... Or following jihad?

01:12:32.196 --> 01:12:34.066
I see both as one treatment.

01:12:34.432 --> 01:12:36.635
Medicine is mercy,

01:12:37.201 --> 01:12:39.304
jihad is duty.

01:12:39.603 --> 01:12:42.039
What about me,
am I a Crusader?

01:12:42.307 --> 01:12:44.276
I came here
to bring clean water.

01:12:44.576 --> 01:12:46.678
Allah will ask payment of you.

01:12:49.647 --> 01:12:51.850
You said I was
going to be spared.

01:12:54.318 --> 01:12:55.954
I need to go home.

01:12:56.920 --> 01:12:58.823
I need to go back to her.

01:13:05.796 --> 01:13:08.567
Who am I to know
the will of God?

01:13:09.334 --> 01:13:11.836
You may die tomorrow.

01:13:13.771 --> 01:13:17.543
Or... you may become
a blessed one.

01:14:02.219 --> 01:14:03.886
So, how long are
you going to stay with us

01:14:03.888 --> 01:14:05.890
on the Faroes,
Professor Flinders?

01:14:06.323 --> 01:14:07.625
At least a week,

01:14:07.991 --> 01:14:08.960
maybe more.

01:14:09.893 --> 01:14:11.593
We found a quiet
place for you,

01:14:11.595 --> 01:14:13.264
where you can
get your work done.

01:14:13.964 --> 01:14:14.932
Thank you.

01:14:15.265 --> 01:14:16.701
Captain's orders.

01:14:17.669 --> 01:14:20.171
Is it possible to dock
by any of those rocks?

01:14:20.537 --> 01:14:22.441
- Just for a few minutes?
- Sure.

01:14:34.485 --> 01:14:36.021
What are you doing?

01:14:36.987 --> 01:14:38.055
I'm counting.

01:14:39.057 --> 01:14:40.025
Lichens.

01:14:40.625 --> 01:14:42.694
Some of the species
here are very rare.

01:14:42.960 --> 01:14:45.828
You think they're shells,
but if you come closer,

01:14:45.830 --> 01:14:49.568
they're like tiny trees,
little forests.

01:14:49.767 --> 01:14:52.970
And this one here is
the marriage between a...

01:14:53.336 --> 01:14:55.640
a fungus and a cyan-bacteria.

01:14:56.374 --> 01:14:59.544
If you would magnify the edges,
you wouldn't be able to see,

01:14:59.777 --> 01:15:01.580
where life begins
and where it ends.

01:15:01.778 --> 01:15:03.648
It just dissolves from...

01:15:04.415 --> 01:15:07.319
from life into non-life.

01:18:02.425 --> 01:18:06.130
<i>"No man is an island,
entire of itself.</i>

01:18:06.429 --> 01:18:09.066
<i>Every man is a piece
of the continent,</i>

01:18:09.866 --> 01:18:11.402
<i>a part of the main.</i>

01:18:12.937 --> 01:18:16.308
Any man's death diminishes me,

01:18:16.874 --> 01:18:19.510
because I am
involved in mankind,

01:18:19.809 --> 01:18:24.982
<i>and therefore never send to
know for whom the bell tolls,</i>

01:18:25.515 --> 01:18:27.052
it tolls for thee."

01:18:27.518 --> 01:18:30.255
Do you keep John Donne
with you wherever you go?

01:18:30.888 --> 01:18:32.624
<i>Yeah.</i>

01:18:52.576 --> 01:18:54.079
Let me go.

01:18:55.312 --> 01:18:56.647
Let me go, please.

01:19:13.196 --> 01:19:17.167
I will be killed soon,
I welcome it.

01:19:19.804 --> 01:19:23.275
I believe you will
die too, Mr. Water.

01:20:26.771 --> 01:20:29.974
Biyole, we will
videotape you soon.

01:20:30.840 --> 01:20:32.610
Do you know <i>Bambi,</i> water boy?

01:20:33.677 --> 01:20:35.213
I saw it when I was young.

01:20:35.845 --> 01:20:38.316
You see, Bambi is
the innocent one.

01:20:38.549 --> 01:20:41.050
When you watch the
forest fire again,

01:20:41.052 --> 01:20:43.552
then you will see his
father protecting him,

01:20:43.554 --> 01:20:45.156
giving up his own life.

01:20:46.557 --> 01:20:49.561
It is like the Crusaders who
are burning the Islamic state.

01:22:27.892 --> 01:22:30.528
Abdul... go.

01:22:37.168 --> 01:22:39.771
I want to convert
you to Islam.

01:22:41.237 --> 01:22:44.342
And I want you to be
merciful and let me go.

01:22:50.481 --> 01:22:52.916
I won't make
a video for you.

01:22:53.150 --> 01:22:55.117
I won't sit in
front of a camera

01:22:55.119 --> 01:22:56.717
and say the things
that you want me to say...

01:22:56.719 --> 01:22:58.021
You're of use to us.

01:22:58.621 --> 01:23:03.193
Shadid told me you can
clean water, stop diseases.

01:23:05.295 --> 01:23:07.097
You will do important
work for us.

01:23:07.531 --> 01:23:10.101
But you are a non-believer.

01:23:10.668 --> 01:23:13.237
I want you to meet
with your Creator.

01:23:13.603 --> 01:23:15.339
- No.
- No?

01:23:19.843 --> 01:23:21.278
No.

01:23:22.146 --> 01:23:24.948
Allah sees you,

01:23:25.415 --> 01:23:27.615
and he's waiting for you
to take the straight path.

01:23:27.617 --> 01:23:30.988
We've got Allah
in common, you and I.

01:23:31.187 --> 01:23:34.791
The Allah of our
common father, Abraham.

01:23:35.826 --> 01:23:37.695
I love Abraham.

01:23:38.128 --> 01:23:41.064
And I love his love
for all his children.

01:23:41.598 --> 01:23:46.637
And yes, I do believe
that Allah sees me.

01:23:47.237 --> 01:23:49.240
Sees us, but...

01:23:50.808 --> 01:23:51.809
no.

01:23:53.009 --> 01:23:55.245
Who are you to know this,

01:23:56.347 --> 01:23:58.383
and reject the Koran?

01:24:39.188 --> 01:24:40.924
Hey, stop!

01:25:04.113 --> 01:25:05.383
No!

01:25:05.715 --> 01:25:06.817
Fuck!

01:25:30.406 --> 01:25:31.842
Let's go.

01:26:45.915 --> 01:26:50.354
<i>Allahu akbar. Allahu akbar.</i>

01:27:01.231 --> 01:27:04.900
<i>Recent geology
research from the University of Cincinnati,</i>

01:27:04.902 --> 01:27:07.569
<i>presents new evidence
for bacteria</i>

01:27:07.571 --> 01:27:10.504
<i>found fossilized in
two separate locations.</i>

01:27:10.506 --> 01:27:14.543
<i>The 2.52-billion-year-old
sulfur-oxidizing bacteria,</i>

01:27:14.545 --> 01:27:18.346
<i>are described as exceptionally
large, spherical-shaped,</i>

01:27:18.348 --> 01:27:20.782
<i>smooth-walled
microscopic structures,</i>

01:27:20.784 --> 01:27:22.383
<i>much larger than most modern...</i>

01:28:18.709 --> 01:28:20.978
You like working
for the MI6, Water?

01:28:23.112 --> 01:28:24.147
You have fun?

01:28:24.647 --> 01:28:28.149
I mean not now, but in
general, you have fun?

01:28:28.552 --> 01:28:30.017
You like the CIA?

01:28:30.019 --> 01:28:31.755
I don't know what
you're talking about.

01:28:31.955 --> 01:28:32.990
Jihad is life.

01:28:33.823 --> 01:28:35.992
Your friends,
they don't care about you.

01:28:42.331 --> 01:28:44.168
Jihad is life after death.

01:28:56.479 --> 01:29:00.748
So, you're not sorry for
being a Donne-loving Brit

01:29:00.750 --> 01:29:02.484
who loves his God and country?

01:29:02.486 --> 01:29:05.055
No. No, I'm not.

01:29:05.522 --> 01:29:07.258
God save the Queen,
and all that.

01:29:07.991 --> 01:29:10.261
<i>I'm not sorry
for that, either.</i>

01:30:22.633 --> 01:30:25.303
She'll be ready to go
down tomorrow, professor.

01:30:25.802 --> 01:30:27.804
Wonderful, thank you.

01:33:19.576 --> 01:33:22.046
Come on!

01:33:32.488 --> 01:33:33.790
Let's go.

01:34:20.336 --> 01:34:21.871
Be safe, Dani.

01:34:56.673 --> 01:34:59.175
I don't want death, Dani.

01:34:59.442 --> 01:35:01.078
Not in this place.

01:35:02.211 --> 01:35:04.982
And not for any cause.

01:35:05.915 --> 01:35:07.217
I wanna...

01:35:11.388 --> 01:35:13.023
I want to be beside you.

01:35:33.977 --> 01:35:35.776
<i>We're listening, Nautile.</i>

01:35:35.778 --> 01:35:38.645
Nautile to Atalante, Nautile to Atalante.
Do you read me?

01:35:38.647 --> 01:35:41.184
Immersion one, zero, zero, zero.

01:35:41.418 --> 01:35:44.552
<i>Understood, Nautile,
1,000 meters deep. Over.</i>

01:35:44.554 --> 01:35:48.021
What have you been writing,
if you don't mind me asking?

01:35:48.023 --> 01:35:49.556
Oh, it's nothing.

01:35:49.558 --> 01:35:50.658
It's just something...

01:35:50.660 --> 01:35:53.026
I felt like I needed to write.

01:35:53.028 --> 01:35:54.665
Can you read it to me?

01:35:59.436 --> 01:36:01.138
"You will be in Hades...

01:36:02.906 --> 01:36:04.975
drowned in oblivion,

01:36:05.642 --> 01:36:07.344
swallowing water,

01:36:08.978 --> 01:36:11.080
erasing all memory.

01:36:12.915 --> 01:36:16.619
You will take your place
among the teeming hordes,

01:36:17.320 --> 01:36:19.689
of nameless micro-organisms."

01:36:20.255 --> 01:36:23.259
Must be bad luck, talking
like this at this depth.

01:37:00.196 --> 01:37:03.300
Thank you, Abdul,
thank you.

01:37:15.111 --> 01:37:17.147
In 20 minutes,
we'll be landing.

01:37:18.313 --> 01:37:20.985
So, I'm just switching
on the main propeller.

01:37:21.718 --> 01:37:22.987
Yeah.

01:37:24.387 --> 01:37:25.485
And the sonar.

01:37:25.487 --> 01:37:27.890
There's a reason
hell is down here.

01:37:28.357 --> 01:37:31.461
There's a reason heaven is up
there, I remember that now.

01:37:43.339 --> 01:37:45.342
Can we turn up
the lights now?

01:37:45.775 --> 01:37:47.210
Certainly.

01:37:54.017 --> 01:37:55.853
<i>Okay,
I dropped the second weight.</i>

01:37:56.452 --> 01:37:58.054
<i>We're listening, Nautile.</i>

01:37:58.321 --> 01:38:02.326
We're about to arrive,
give us our new coordinates.

01:38:03.460 --> 01:38:07.227
<i>Navigation reset,
71 degrees north, 45 minutes,</i>

01:38:07.229 --> 01:38:09.133
<i>two degrees west, 28 minutes.</i>

01:38:09.499 --> 01:38:13.066
<i>You're almost at 3,400
meters now. Over.</i>

01:38:13.068 --> 01:38:14.670
Thanks, guys, we got that.

01:38:15.604 --> 01:38:17.607
We're close now.

01:38:22.144 --> 01:38:24.147
- Careful now.
- Yeah.

01:38:26.014 --> 01:38:28.449
Unbelievable.

01:38:28.451 --> 01:38:29.653
Amazing.

01:38:38.094 --> 01:38:40.761
There's a hydrothermal vent
straight ahead,

01:38:40.763 --> 01:38:41.665
just to the right.

01:38:42.932 --> 01:38:44.635
Shall we, Étienne?

01:38:45.000 --> 01:38:46.803
Yeah, sure.

01:38:55.344 --> 01:38:57.347
I'm opening the basket.

01:39:01.416 --> 01:39:06.322
And I'll start operating
the arm and collect.

01:39:10.125 --> 01:39:13.560
You can help me, Dani,
direct the camera to it.

01:39:13.562 --> 01:39:15.398
Oh, right, sorry.

01:39:16.299 --> 01:39:20.204
Can you get the arm to grab
a piece of that chimney?

01:39:20.769 --> 01:39:22.505
Yeah, sure.

01:39:25.008 --> 01:39:27.778
Okay, here comes Godzilla.

01:39:32.781 --> 01:39:34.117
Okay.

01:39:35.684 --> 01:39:38.187
We got it.

01:39:46.995 --> 01:39:49.599
Here it is,
mission accomplished.

01:39:51.968 --> 01:39:53.370
Fabulous.

01:39:54.836 --> 01:39:57.707
I so wish I could have
shared this with him.

01:39:58.073 --> 01:40:00.143
What would you
have told him now?

01:40:01.110 --> 01:40:03.147
I would have told him that...

01:40:03.946 --> 01:40:06.449
down here,
it's not photosynthetic,

01:40:06.648 --> 01:40:09.952
like everything on the surface,
but chemosynthetic.

01:40:10.820 --> 01:40:14.154
I would have told him
that life down here

01:40:14.156 --> 01:40:17.760
exists without light,
and that it grows,

01:40:19.228 --> 01:40:22.762
because of the
chemical energy just

01:40:22.764 --> 01:40:26.667
pouring out of those cracks,
from the core of our Earth.

01:40:26.669 --> 01:40:28.872
And he would have
understood that?

01:40:29.805 --> 01:40:31.174
Yes.

01:40:33.076 --> 01:40:35.042
- What's happening?
- I don't know.

01:40:35.044 --> 01:40:36.546
Are we all right?

01:40:42.986 --> 01:40:44.318
Okay, we need to reboot.

01:40:44.320 --> 01:40:46.456
- You want some light?
- Yeah, please.

01:40:48.090 --> 01:40:49.927
Switch off all the instruments.

01:40:50.994 --> 01:40:51.929
Okay.

01:40:52.161 --> 01:40:55.265
I turn on the emergency
battery, switch on.

01:40:59.168 --> 01:41:00.603
Are there any other solutions?

01:41:01.237 --> 01:41:03.738
Do we need to drop the remaining
weight and go to the surface?

01:41:03.740 --> 01:41:05.576
No, no, no,
we're still drifting.

01:41:05.907 --> 01:41:07.173
We can't see anything.

01:41:07.175 --> 01:41:10.112
We could float up, hit a chimney
that could fall on us, trap us.

01:41:10.446 --> 01:41:11.881
We can't move at all anymore.

01:41:12.714 --> 01:41:15.585
Right, let's go through
the sequence again.

01:41:22.592 --> 01:41:26.429
We will take our place
among the teeming hordes.

01:41:28.497 --> 01:41:31.101
We will be the foundation
for all forms.

01:41:31.634 --> 01:41:35.606
We will be in Hades,
drowned in oblivion,

01:41:37.072 --> 01:41:40.643
swallowing water,
erasing all memory.

01:41:41.978 --> 01:41:43.914
It will be a submergence.

01:41:51.353 --> 01:41:54.691
<i>I've thought about
bodies buried at sea.</i>

01:41:56.625 --> 01:41:59.495
<i>It's not dust to dust,
that's for sure.</i>

01:42:00.929 --> 01:42:02.499
It's water to water.

01:42:08.370 --> 01:42:10.840
We are all being made of water.

01:42:13.308 --> 01:42:15.044
<i>Like you said.</i>

01:42:31.094 --> 01:42:32.760
Because you're a wanderer

01:42:32.762 --> 01:42:34.798
who strayed from
the straight path,

01:42:35.397 --> 01:42:37.066
the only path to God...

01:42:38.334 --> 01:42:40.403
you're not going
to see Paradise.

01:42:53.849 --> 01:42:55.485
You know Arabic, Water.

01:42:57.553 --> 01:42:59.488
And you read the Koran.

01:43:01.557 --> 01:43:03.660
Okay, once more.

01:43:06.595 --> 01:43:07.964
On.

01:43:17.506 --> 01:43:20.074
Dani, we're on
emergency battery.

01:43:20.076 --> 01:43:21.478
We can't stay.

01:43:21.677 --> 01:43:23.410
Yes, we...

01:43:23.412 --> 01:43:25.014
we have all the samples.

01:43:27.250 --> 01:43:28.852
Let's take her up.

01:43:29.251 --> 01:43:31.120
Yeah, good.

01:44:14.196 --> 01:44:15.431
I'll see you again.

